			"text": "Plectronoceras is one of the earliest cephalopod-related mollusk and comes from the upper Cambrian. With shell only being up to 4 cm, it is known from various fossils of its curved shell. No fossils are complete and the apex and aperture are not known. Soft tissues are also not known, so it was sometimes reconstructed like a snail. However, its shell has septa and a siphuncle to maintain buoyancy, which meant it could float and probably had nautiloid-like body instead."
